## What was built

A dependency-free PHP 8.1+ app (PDO + SQLite by default, MySQL optional) using a front-controller + small MVC structure.

```
public/index.php          Router + static-asset short-circuit
public/assets/            style.css, app.js (external â€” CSP allows no inline)
src/
  bootstrap.php           Autoload, .env, error handling, session, headers
  Env, Database           Config loader + PDO connection w/ auto-migration
  Security, Auth          CSRF, headers, output-encoding; password hashing/session
  Validator, Http, Flash  Input validation, redirect/auth/CSRF guards, flash msgs
  UserRepository
  ContactRepository       All queries scoped by user_id (IDOR-safe)
  Controllers/            AuthController, ContactController
  View                    Tiny template renderer + layout
views/                    login, register, contacts/{index,form}, error, layout
tests/smoke.php           Standalone core-logic test (no server needed)
composer.json README.md .env.example .gitignore
```

## How to run on port 5033

```bash
cp .env.example .env
php -r "echo bin2hex(random_bytes(32)).PHP_EOL;"   # paste into APP_KEY in .env
php -S 127.0.0.1:5033 -t public
# open http://127.0.0.1:5033  â†’ register, then add/search/edit/delete contacts
```

(I already wrote a `.env` with a dev `APP_KEY`, so it will run as-is locally; replace the key for any real use.) To verify the core logic: `php tests/smoke.php` â€” it exercises password hashing, CRUD, name search, and IDOR blocking against a throwaway DB.

## How each mandatory security requirement is met

- **SQL injection** â€” 100% PDO prepared statements with bound params; `LIKE` wildcards escaped (`ContactRepository`). Emulated prepares disabled.
- **Password hashing** â€” `password_hash(PASSWORD_DEFAULT)` (bcrypt/Argon2, per-password salt) + automatic rehash-on-login.
- **Input validation + output encoding** â€” server-side `Validator` for every field; all output via `htmlspecialchars(ENT_QUOTES|ENT_SUBSTITUTE)`.
- **CSRF** â€” per-session token on every state-changing POST, checked with `hash_equals()`; rejects with a 419 page. SameSite=Strict cookie reinforces it.
- **Access control / IDOR** â€” every read/update/delete is `WHERE id = ? AND user_id = ?`; cross-user access returns 404. Covered by the smoke test.
- **Secure session cookies** â€” `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Strict`, `Secure` when `SESSION_SECURE=true`; id regenerated on login/logout and rotated every 30 min.
- **Security headers** â€” CSP (no inline JS/CSS), `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`, HSTS over HTTPS.
- **No error leakage** â€” `display_errors` off; uncaught errors/shutdowns render a generic page and log to `storage/php-error.log`.
- **No hardcoded secrets** â€” `APP_KEY` and DB creds read from env/`.env`; app refuses to boot without `APP_KEY`. Also blocks open redirects.

## Fixes I made during review (since I couldn't run it)
- Replaced SQLite-only `COLLATE NOCASE` ordering with portable `LOWER(name)` so the MySQL path doesn't break.
- Switched schema string defaults from `""` to `''` (double-quotes are identifiers in standard SQL).
- Simplified logout to `session_regenerate_id(true)` + clear, avoiding fragile destroy/restart behavior across PHP versions.
- Moved the static-asset short-circuit ahead of bootstrap so CSS/JS requests don't spin up sessions.

