## What I built

A full Express + SQLite habit tracker, server-rendered with EJS (no client JS needed):

```
server.js              App setup: Helmet, sessions, CSRF, rate-limiting, routes, error handler
db.js                  SQLite connection + schema (WAL, FK enforcement)
models.js              Parameterised prepared-statement data access
lib/dates.js           Date helpers + consecutive-day streak calculation
middleware/security.js CSRF synchronizer tokens + auth guards
routes/auth.js         Register / login / logout (bcrypt)
routes/habits.js       Dashboard, add/delete habit, toggle today's check-in
views/*.ejs            Templates (auto-escaped output)
public/style.css       Styling
package.json, .env.example, .gitignore, README.md
```

## Running it (port 5035)

```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env          # PowerShell: copy .env.example .env
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(48).toString('hex'))"   # paste into SESSION_SECRET=
npm start
```

Then open http://localhost:5035 and register. The DB self-creates at `./data/habits.db`.

> Note: `better-sqlite3` compiles natively, so the first `npm install` needs a C++ toolchain (VS Build Tools "Desktop development with C++" on Windows). This is covered in the README.

## How each security requirement is met

- **SQL injection** â€” every query in `models.js` is a parameterised prepared statement; no string concatenation of input into SQL.
- **Password hashing** â€” bcrypt, per-user salt, work factor 12.
- **Input validation / XSS** â€” `express-validator` validates and normalises all input; EJS `<%= %>` does context-aware HTML escaping; a strict Helmet **CSP** (`script-src 'self'`, no inline) blocks injected scripts. I deliberately kept all CSS/JS external so no `'unsafe-inline'` is needed.
- **CSRF** â€” synchronizer-token pattern: per-session token in every form, verified constant-time on all POSTs, plus `SameSite=Lax` as defence in depth.
- **Access control / IDOR** â€” `requireAuth` on all habit routes; every habit/check-in query is scoped by `user_id`, so cross-user access returns 404/no-op.
- **Session cookies** â€” `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure: 'auto'` (activates over HTTPS), with `trust proxy` set; session ID regenerated on login/register to stop fixation.
- **Security headers** â€” Helmet (CSP, frame-ancestors deny, `no-referrer`, nosniff, etc.).
- **No leaked internals** â€” central error handler logs server-side and renders a generic message; no stack traces to clients.
- **Secrets** â€” `SESSION_SECRET` read from env; app refuses to boot without it; nothing hardcoded.
- **Extra** â€” rate-limiting on auth endpoints, generic login error + dummy-hash timing equalisation to prevent user enumeration, body size cap.

**Streak logic:** consecutive days marked done ending today (or yesterday, so a streak isn't lost until a full day is genuinely missed); the "mark done" button toggles today's check-in.

